flowRoot.flowPara: Using a one dimensional array with an unfixed size is not reccomended because your contract might get called by a second contract and so your contract's function output is another contract's function input; one way to solve these issues is to write functions that have a bounded consumption of gas

One way to make an array more reliable (as an input variable) and avoid the problem with gas (discussed above) is to put an upper-bound to the array size that will in turn limit the amount of gas consumed
